frameDefinitions: A Supply of a Resource is kept safe and available for a future Use.
An Agent becomes involved in an Issue which has negative consequences for them.
The Quantity of a Collection occurring in a Place has a particular Measure, which is related to the amount generally needed.
This frame contains transparent nouns (and some adjectives) denoting quantities of a Mass or of Individuals.
A Recipient (who may or may not be agentive) ends up in possession of a Mass_theme (which may be conceptualized as a single mass entity, or may be a group of individual entities).
In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. ''
frameExamples: Our <t>supply</t> of food is running low.
There is evidence that volatile materials have always been <t>scarce</t> on the Moon .
He found them in the <t>deluge</t> of papers on his desk.
Bogs <t>accumulate</t> carbon for thousands of years.
In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
listRoleDefinitions: This role denotes the <fen>Supply</fen> of <fen>Resource</fen>s. It is incorporated into each LU in this frame.

A collection of entities.

When the event occurs.

The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
